-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=Oh1ttzjLU18nk2RhBDj1lA\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=182.62642\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"100000584478905943284","name":"GPS Plumbing, Inc. (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/100000584478905943284"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"26016 132nd St SE","city":"Monroe","postal_code":"98272","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Daniel Jackson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0eVtU24NoRDz2Ol2S-GFBOBlW5DYC9H82itb3NG0-meI7h8s=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mike from GPS came out same day to help me when my hot water heater died. He was friendly, professional, and fast. By the end of the day my house was back to normal. He got all the parts himself, installed it up to code, and charged a fair price.\n\n10/10, GPS Plumbing is now my go-to for plumbing services.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrh0TyKpFaK0h1pA8AfKjhVfJrsNGR6BSAnJVRfy8AWecyaw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Last week my hot water heater rusted out and flooded the garage. Mike from GPS Plumbing replaced the water heater the next day. His work was spotless, he arrived on time, and the job was well priced. Better than that, he returned the next week to replace the kitchen sink which was nasty, the garbage disposal was broken, the hot water dispenser was broken when I bought the house a year ago, and the faucet was dripping. The result was perfect!!! Again, Mike was on time, did an excellent job for a reasonable price. I’d give him more stars if I could! Highly recommend.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3Y0zVlLaU_nC9QtY1ySgSfilckg2JxkjqP2zlbH2aFgdcnzUl_1o2bsPfNSJelv3I1HGUocAqvJzSffPwvY7MTo_0aMOa8WJVB-ATS491TWVYdI0e5UBmLBlYMnq8rsgqO8N4=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1BWuTAQ1k0BQsmxbDWnOIddXuRzrgNXoFPHjZFxlpDZr4O4XtEaoLVBGDTRGV_9r3VvHlOfKmiTSF8AVnN9BVVD9C2tLPUl9opgfNc6bhcJUvH1L_2w9WLoarpy1IeYraqSgVpCA=k-no"],"When":"2024-12-19"},{"Name":"Chris Pace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjXcB1Ynz3hf7_-yUficAx-mA5b68oeLGeVABr464KB1qI4g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mike with GPS Plumbing is absolutely the best!\nI first had Mike out to our home back in 2013 to repair our utility room plumbing for the washer and sink. I remember being impressed then with his abilities, professionalism and the replacement parts he used. He does not use the cheap parts that the big box stores use. When he does a repair, he uses top of the line parts and is very versed with the use of PEX. Since his first visit, I have had Mike out several times as we had a total gut and remodel to the rest of our home. Mike is the one we went to do the entire re-plumbing of our home implementing PEX everywhere, new hot water tank and the relocation of that tank to the utility room, re-circulating pumps, all of the kitchen and bathroom fixtures, toilets showers....and the latest was the re-wire of our garage and adding a second panel where Mike came out and transferred our well equipment into and along one wall of the garage with all new equipment and whole home filtration with UV and a very cool water meter! It really is a work of art and anybody on a well can appreciate having new well equipment with total filtration. Not only that, he figured out why our water pressure was lacking and fixed that issue and now the pressure is amazing. In this repair/rebuild of our well equipment, he also repaired a problem with our well and put in a very cool yard hydrant for use on part of our property for guests staying in their RV when visiting.\nOur next project will be the outdoor shower on our deck by our hot tub and the only one I will have out is Mike. Over the years of having him out, I have gotten to know Mike pretty well. He is really is the best out there and if you want the best working on or repairing the biggest investment you'll ever make, then give him a call. You'll be glad you did and you will have peace of mind knowing he did the repair.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0aFdyDBe-x_XWLxzXu0d571OoDWj7QKlh73FF6qKNXIQahxsT8qVk0oiGYrsLvJ0XI0cNGX4k2sQw9KwTLVygWk6JVnWDKrh6uNJTy40NWn4yi_w9dRuzYvC5SscTLr9YRwWdd=k-no"],"When":"2018-9-11"},{"Name":"Annette Beaven","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIXCEwQkyJ7fUUOzS2wQiR6XiJVvjkkn-8qzgTZOKNzUUEi_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mike from GPS Plumbing has consistently provided excellent service. Over the years, I've had two leaks in the water line between the house and the meter, and on both occasions, Mike was incredibly helpful in locating and repairing the issues. He is highly knowledgeable, resourceful, and skilled. He was on time, easy to work with, and his prices are fair. Mike truly goes above and beyond to ensure everything is done impeccably. I highly recommend him!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark Schergen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBSUNgoro5yHUAQNLgKFqfkrlaDucQKUBb8NvqjrOS-3QgrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have contracted GPS plumbing as needed since January 2013. Mike has replaced several water heaters, replaced failed angle stop valves, replaced a faucet and repaired a bath tub / shower valve. All the tasks were accomplished properly in a single service call. Labor and selected Material quality is excellent. Work Ethic is excellent. Mike is efficient. We have coordinated and scheduled work with GPS in advance. Mike arrives on time and is ready to repair. Mike keeps a work space neat, cleans and removes dunnage as a repair is accomplished. Mike communicates before he starts, as a repair progresses and when he finishes.  After a repair is completed, it is tested and inspected. I have been pleased with Mike’s quality of work and Professionalism. We will continue to contact GPS Plumbing, Inc. for our plumbing needs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jack Hills","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKtfKqUcVkMzKuNjhfuLE4TzbrB2Nb0XSZkYaOA9Ke9hSqQ3g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had Mike of GPS Plumbing replace our gas water heater five years ago in our house in Monroe. He was quick to respond and get the job done quickly. Recently we found that an outside faucet was leaking, thanks to the City of Monroe suggesting our bills indicated we may have a leak. Again Mike was quick to respond and replace the leaking faucet.  \"So, Mike, while you're here let's just install another faucet on the other side of the house for convenience!\"\nOh what a terrible  crawl space I have! Next day; DONE!\nI highly recommend Mike, GPS Plumbing to take care of your plumbing issues.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeff Skagen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDowVOhFfyHNE3H5N7Qb2VU4tw-GONPukY5JJ3JNk5ZuILOZma=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mike from GPS Plumbing has been out to my home twice, and I've been quite happy with his work both times. The first time I found my household PRV leaking, and Mike came out and replaced it the next day since I could only stop the leak by turning off the houses water supply. More recently, one of my toilet tanks started leaking at a bolt penetration where it connects to the bowl. Mike had me send him some photo's of the toilet, so he'd know what he was dealing with and what replacement parts he needed to bring, and made sure I had the leak stopped and had other working toilets in the house so that I didn't need an emergency call out. I actually decided to have him replace the hardware and gaskets on all three of my toilets, as they were all equally old and worn, and also asked him to replace my garbage disposal with a new one I'd just picked up. He did all that work in only about 3 hours, for a fee that matched his estimate and that I felt was reasonable for the work he did. As long as I live in Monroe, Mike will be my go-to guy for any plumbing work I need done!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anne A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLUdG-ZDbYd8-e1V55M3-gxJNiSriQzq9Ey7idpz4mRSPIs9QA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"GPS Plumbing was recommended by my condo association for water heater replacements and plumbing needs. I called GPS to replace several bathroom sinks and a toilet. Mike responded quickly with the cost for the job, and I was fortunate to get an appointment for the following day. Mike  provides outstanding service with his knowledge and experience in plumbing as well as his great communication and people skills.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
