"country":""},"about":[{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Jeff Summers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWP7kyPKDUXtOIAM_JXoxuw2IFOvYMY_vZdFq7H5YYQzsz41dFS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ian and Damon were wonderful to work with for my furnace installation.  I was quite impressed with the mentoring process Ian had with Damon, he will have his own truck soon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Julian Spitzli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUEuu2IX3APh7U7fAOBz_8UWJwj1pdH08_v3W8GK-AnnkVTbbU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I would recommend considering a different company. Based on my experience, this company appeared far more focused on collecting payment than standing behind their work.\n\nWe moved into our home in late 2024 and had our furnace replaced shortly after moving in. The total cost was approximately $7,000–$8,000, including additional exhaust work that was not originally planned. About a year later, we began experiencing heating issues, including cold air blowing from the vents. Since Beacon installed the furnace, we contacted them for service.\n\nThe first two technicians scheduled to come out never showed up, and communication consisted only of brief text messages. On the third attempt, a technician did arrive, but we were quoted nearly $500 just to inspect the furnace. Rather than performing a meaningful diagnosis, he recommended installing additional temperature sensors throughout the home, despite the furnace displaying an active fault code that could have been investigated. I declined the service due to the high cost and lack of proper troubleshooting.\n\nWe then contacted a different company, who immediately opened the furnace and identified the problem. Part of the exhaust had been routed back into the furnace cabinet, preventing the system from operating correctly. Once this issue was repaired, the heating system worked without further problems. That company also identified several installation errors and corrected them at no additional charge. One significant issue was that an incorrect exhaust fitting had been installed—a tee fitting was used where a wye fitting should have been, connecting the furnace and hot water tank to the same exhaust line.\n\nI contacted Beacon again to address the improperly installed exhaust. When the technician arrived, we were immediately presented with a $600 quote. It became clear that the customer service representative had not explained the situation to the technician, requiring me to re-explain the entire issue. Only then did Beacon agree to cover the repair cost. At that point, my confidence in the company was already gone, and I initially declined the repair due to a complete lack of trust in their workmanship.\n\nAfter spending an additional 30 minutes on the phone with customer service, I reluctantly agreed to allow them to correct the exhaust. However, the appointment was rescheduled three times, and for the most recent appointment, the technician never showed up.\n\nGiven the repeated no-shows, poor communication, questionable workmanship, and overall experience, I cannot recommend this company. I strongly encourage others to take their business to a company that stands behind its work. I will not be using or recommending Beacon again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emily Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXuJjyG4iVBSeH613YIzwbQ7Vbjsd6MeebuiPAH607sFp8i-zs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had leak spring up under my kitchen sink that was spraying water everywhere and I immediately called Beacon. Jesus and Alfredo were so fast and kind I would definitely recommend them!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lionel Abdool","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWUOWNotjrQ2BIizABys9tRudcODwDuSUrM7s25omwPMq9hJoI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Romeo and Bailey did a great job installing a water heater and safety equipment that had failed out on us. We very respectful and prompt, we're in an out in 2 hours.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christopher Freeman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVxEFZY_XZ7rG_WWcItKJUIqonCGtQdnIYGbrYor6Uw8133A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Chris and Tim replaced our drains and diagnosed some other issues. They were easy to communicate with and followed through with everything. Would definitely work with them again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Timothy Blandford Jr.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWk5r8j6idKnHJoxV8K6cQQIthv69tWsPrGP-QwkJj4VLKfZY25=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a shower valve that failed and was actively leaking. Unfortunately, our main valve was faulty too, not allowing us to turn the water off completely. Gio and Zach were here within an hour, diagnosed the issue, quickly stopped the active leak, and helped coordinate with another vendor for water damage remediation. They even gave some guidance on working with the water remediation folks for filing a home insurance claim. Gio gave incredible full stack service, all with a very calming and positive attitude. Highly recommend!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Taylor Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJqdTCBg6pF7K13oG9Gs74AQ5Y3wn0qud7zVaelZbUBgmHMV_NA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ian and Damon were wonderful. They did an excellent job. Highly recommend working with them!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ha Al","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKKB83MTppJoOlvWA90FZU8xSoaupo8MpjIB3qmyXKW-dQO4A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Zadrien was one of the best plumbers that I’ve dealt with! He made a stressful situation feel not so bad with his professionalism and his cool demeanor! Thank you so much Zadrien for coming out after hours , beacon plumping should be proud that you represent their company.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
