=w440-h298-k-no"},{"title":"Street View \u0026 360°","image":"https://streetviewpixels-pa.googleapis.com/v1/thumbnail?panoid=VPg4oiJiq9BaM2XfCDlG3w\u0026cb_client=maps_sv.tactile.gps\u0026w=224\u0026h=298\u0026yaw=247.82285\u0026pitch=0\u0026thumbfov=100"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":[{"link":"https://mikesplumbinganddrain.com/","source":"mikesplumbinganddrain.com"}],"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"112154306474331444747","name":"Mike's Plumbing \u0026 Drain Cleaning (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112154306474331444747"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"21010 70th Ave W","city":"Edmonds","postal_code":"98026","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":true},{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Grace Cabisada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5nRikrsDodGpqhVf2VHXRQ-I1CQA7t4vJ_kQ8ypMIRMxaF-f2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mike's Plumbing has been a reliable and trusted partner for plumbing services for many years. As one of our vendors at GPS Renting, they consistently ensure that they assist us in every way possible. Nicole, Kaitlyn, and Whitney are particularly responsive and helpful, making our collaboration seamless and efficient. Worth to be recommended! Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Isaac Benton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU27mbCctkEyMjzf4OhAPa9EIUfH_c9IDLPA7RApODxjl1qvOJc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Spent several hours troubleshooting my backed up kitchen sink last night to no relief. I contacted the main office this morning where I chatted with Sandra(Cindy? sry) and Taylor as we talked about my issue and they coordinated with dispatch. Several hours later Steve and Aiden arrived, assessed the situation, and got me working again in a couple of hours of hard work.\nThroughout the process I could tell communication between the main office and techs was solid, Steve and Aiden arrived fully apprised of my conversation with the office and got straight to troubleshooting after pleasant introductions.\nAs I sat at my computer last night stewing in frustration that I couldn't fix the issue myself, while searching for local reputable expertise I came across multiple reviews of Mike's Plumbing highlighting qualities of transparency and honesty. From my first call to farewell, these qualities resonated in every interaction. I will be using Mike's Plumbing again. Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Danny Tse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIUlWLO3EICUAk-Ov0bfBDqaf_TB5uf8J8WuZtsNzQFfq5u=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Alec and Thomas came to help with two leaky faucets and replace old FlowTite valves. They were incredibly professional, courteous, and took the time to explain unexpected issues clearly and calmly. Their work was excellent, and we’re very pleased with the service. A big shout-out as well to Tyler, who answered my call and patiently addressed some initial questions—his reassurance set the tone for a great experience. We’ve definitely found our go-to plumbing company!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kevin Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLPfBOVU06f4qdRDDlCSBIFV3SYT_G1Hs4MpXgpWQddeIRD9w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Hired Mike's Plumbing with confidence (due to the reviews online) in 2023 to fix a 2nd floor shower drain which was leaking and needed replacement.\n\nHowever, 2 years later there is water leaking from that same spot. We've not had any other plumbers to come work on that area and was told I would be charged as a new customer and it would be over $600 for a plumber to come and fix it AGAIN.\n\nThis is a leak in the exact same area which was supposedly fixed previously, if we are being charged full price again, why would I go back to them? What would give us confidence they would even fix the issue this time? (Totally understand if it is a different or new issue causing the leak but to be charged regardless even if they root cause it to be due to the same work/parts that they supplied previously, is frustrating and disappointing).\n\nDo yourself a favor and go with a different company that stands by the integrity of their work.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jacob Perin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlB2s6-R9ZlOTcp34x34MgP5Xkp80qjXHxIEZ7qkT02awRU8Ha=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I was working with a competitor, “The Plumbing Physician” (who did great work).\n\nThey recommended Mike’s Plumbing for a plumbing scope because they’d do it at the cheapest rate $260.\n\nThey did not tell me that Mike’s Plumbing would not send me the video.\n\nI called on four occasions, each time Mike’s Plumbing promised to send the scope. On the third call, I verified my email and account with them. They told me Kaitlyn (who was out at the time) is the person who assists with this.\n\nSo, I waited a week for Kaitlyn to return and called again. Kaitlyn said it’d be sent over, but that was not the case.\n\n1 month later, $260 spent, and no video. I guess it was a bargain for a reason.\n\nEDIT: Looks like a negative review got the ball rolling. Thank you for sending the sewer scope.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Janet Cavallo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHjwZKRgzLYozqc7Cyx1hH3QncB6PED2f-V4adDwIq10eVBZQC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been very happy with Mike's Plumbing and have been recommending them to friends since my first service in 2021. I had used 4 other companies since buying my home in 2017, before finding Mike's and using them for maintenance hydro jetting of my backed-up sewer line; the line is old and branches were causing back ups annually (however, when Mike's did the job, it did not back up again for 3 years - obviously doing a better job than the other companies.) Mike's Plumbing did the best job and were honest and professional. They didn't try to sell me services I didn't need, like the other plumbing companies. When I had an emergency I called them without hesitation, knowing I would get fair, professional, and thorough service - and I was right! They quickly and efficiently diagnosed the problem - the water line needed to be replaced - they gave me an estimate, answered all of my questions, and did a great job, completed on time for a fair price. They were even concerned about digging up the plants in my yard and discussed it with me before starting the job. Mike's Plumbing far surpasses other companies I've tried and I would highly recommend them for any plumbing need.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Destiny Hollowed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUsiLWA_BO7yEWy7Fg0b6hrRsNImlcH3mO1Va_Xq_DnQ4Ii9Cc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hired Mike's Plumbing for a replumb job under the kitchen sink. From getting the bid to scheduling service to completion of work, the experience was 5-stars worthy. Not only was scheduling easy, but the team was extremely knowledgeable, professional, and helpful every step of the way. They took time to answer all of my questions. The work itself was impeccable. I was impressed with the quality of work--the guys that came out took care to select the proper piping for the job and replaced horizontal runs, aged parts, and unnecessary sections of the drain to drastically improve it. After getting bids from 4 other local plumbers and getting to understand the work they would've performed, Mike's was and is the clear winner when it comes to great work at a fair price. Will definitely hire them for future home projects.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alke Hartmann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVdS16mxJ0uWvQNNC3JQF50Cz6mWoTzfgHiwxQBwaLLI-m1w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We needed a sewer line repair and installation of a 50 ft. liner. Cody from Mike's Plumbing came out and provided us with a free estimate. He scoped the line, explained the work, answered my questions, and was quick in providing a fair estimate. Everyone I talked to, from scheduling, excavation crew, installers to accounting,  was friendly and eager to answer all my questions. I particularly liked how all the workers were so professional in explaining the different steps, the equipment used, and the timeline that was required. They even provided us with a video of the installation upon completion. This was a job well done!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2x6kCXfWbb4989uDEoLalh1PJ_heEBU4bzUtUsV8QmQD1W63xQ9YvMIqQlPLRnB05KmYxJ_lbK--3GEXvq5Ut0qbILxXgTXKnfr7K2ulGWuoXRLbbL-QB4ikfM4vNUFkZPmT__Qg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn30OsdEIQIHN_Itony9kjmIeA36iImv8Sz6-c-tQZhXIPfid6n6ZlskzizbXF0CBroQW4Fx3blZHHbs-CDpVkOZPu5rY5cmTEHB-T6WXjx68Z4UblnDoqR-d3lK9VE-JiUwznQ=k-no"],"When":"2023-2-3"}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
