ve Vlosky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPHrX9RC36_rPhu87ON9iLY-lNeZ54m6yLhuB_oTDqHhom1stJ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Garrett went above and beyond the call of duty taking caring of a clogged toilet line at my house. What initially seemed like an easy fix turned into an entire day ordeal; when plan A didn’t work Garrett was prepared with plan B/C/D/E - this guy would not give up fixing the problem and amazingly kept the price to the initially agreed upon amount. His communication before arriving, and throughout the process, was A+. Salish Plumbing is incredibly lucky to have an asset like Garret and now will be the first company I call when any/all plumbing issues arise in the future.\n\n10/10 would recommend with zero hesitation.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Becca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIwxV6uTpJUmCuB-mp-eS8lJPzN9bL1GR0D_aXdoD5gehe4eQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We highly recommend Salish Plumbing and would gladly use them again for any future plumbing needs. Our plumber, Patrick, was professional, courteous, punctual, and reasonable with pricing. He was also timely with both diagnosis and service. In our case, the installation was completed the very next day—on Christmas Eve—which made a significant difference for our family’s holidays. Communication throughout the entire process was excellent. Thank you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nicky L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJYI74-ZR6WYj5cUx1q5Diz3vb4OvNSgJjc-MIZ-YZNsX4RPw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Plumer was aware of the home owner's age and langguage barrier. I'm a renter at the home and was referred to this company. The worker who goes by the name Blake, came over to fix a small leak  underneath the bathroom sink.\n\nUnsure if he successfully fixed the leak, it was ovbious the top portion of the sink was'nt. He didnt even attach the plug stopper to the sink.\n\nI would never recommend this company to anyone. Sadly, Blake took their money and ran on to the next victim!\n\nDear Business Owner ,\nAfter reading your reponse regarding my recent experience with one of your technicians,I wanted to follow up directly.\nI initially contacted your company to express my dissatisfaction with the technician's work performance. It  became clear that we had differing perspectives regarding the micommunication that occurred. However, I truly appreciate that your manager promptly reached out to me and assured me that he was committed to resolving the matter.\n\nYour manager listened carefully to my concerns and followed through on his promise to mske things right. Thanks to his efforts and professionalism, what began as a negative experience ultimately turned into a positive one.\n\nWith that being said, I am now a satisfied customer and  can confidently say that your company demobstrates strong customer service values. That level of care and accountability is greatly appreciated.\n\nSincerely,\nNick Lacy","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0Q7K1AOVp8NNIAOiShaj7xkzftcthfpdp0CTfGXyic_HCPMcN18Z7e5o4qoA0ElfIyDYQqDAaGu3dGcjC0SAueshLbr5oVmCUDKwgn9c-sDxpozQsNJxC5sM3A45LqbCs2EHev6Pwp-GE0=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2bHH4kTWH9FPNuRbjoUlX8pox44YnAEucqBkHOKanso9ZCQGdCiyNZoAgp7bUTni3WI8N6x6KC37j5WaFfEA4kTrrYJGT_k_eeDJXFzO-1v23FbCPtsRj63dsJnjXuuDIizootczIoF-Io=k-no"],"When":"2026-2-11"},{"Name":"Robert Mosher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVeroi3388kuF8ANpBbpWqoiZ3swXnfSUtQquYDqedfdYm8u4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️\nOutstanding Service with a Sense of Humor to Match\n\nWe recently had Salish Plumbing out for what turned out to be a slightly embarrassing service call — a severely clogged toilet caused by my wife accidentally flushing what can only be described as a ball of socks. 😅\n\nGarrett was the technician who came out, and from start to finish he was absolutely fantastic. He showed up on time, explained exactly what was going on, and handled the situation with total professionalism — and zero judgment, which we very much appreciated.\n\nNot only did Garrett quickly diagnose and fix the problem, but he also made the whole experience lighthearted and stress-free. It’s not every day you need a plumber who can remove socks from a toilet and your dignity from the floor at the same time.\n\nThe repair was done efficiently, cleanly, and correctly, and Garrett made sure everything was working perfectly before he left. Great communication, great attitude, and clearly someone who takes pride in his work.\n\nIf you need plumbing help — whether it’s a routine issue or a “how did THAT get in there?” moment — Salish Plumbing and Garrett are the team you want to call. Highly recommend! 🚽🧦👏","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"g sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9Rsja-f8X54CscyR_t7IeTe8p7ftjiIQCv3pCpsqPCs0CzUqDrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Salish Plumbing is the best!!! Dealing with a plumbing emergency is never easy, but the team at Salish was exceptionally responsive and communicative (even though it was the holidays and schedules were tight). Everyone I worked with -- Nathan, Dustin, Erik, and Ellie to name just a few -- took their time to explain every issue in detail, walk me through all the repair options, and then schedule the job in record time. I can't recommend this business highly enough: they're highly skilled local professionals. I will definitely work with Salish again when I need an expert on the job!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cutter Werdel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9SMGlKrRVEmFzf0K2aduFTKjcjmsBsbMVg_rSA59KrRtzGBs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I can’t thank Salish Plumbing enough for their help and guidance. When I needed support, they didn’t hesitate to step in and help me work through my questions with genuine care and professionalism. Specifically to Jake, I want to say thank you for going above and beyond to make sure I had everything I needed. Truly appreciate the time and support from the team.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kiran Chitluri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmQ5B3n6ACPAnKr6_K7g4TDZ8fTiksuHYbqeziOcl6nPzHk00eTw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing team that works at Sewer Friendly! I highly recommend them.  Worked a huge project for me and a neighbor together. Caleb at the office was ultra responsive and a big reason we chose this company.  The job was professional and I appreciated the crew especially Roto, Luis, Gabriel, Chucho and Guss.  They are a family run business and you can tell they enjoy what they do.  I compared to a bunch of other sewer companies.  These were the most engaged and caring for our needs.  They go the extra mile.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"B H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsx-shtrAFaW1EmgL8yFBqGebAFz1-TG0oB7l_6Je2ne-lWKE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Unfortunately, I do not recommend Salish Plumbing. After a quick inspection, their plumber claimed I needed a $16,000 sewer replacement—without using a camera or proper diagnostics. When I asked about clearing the blockage—he only suggested removing the upstairs toilet to try clearing it, with no guarantee of success and entirely at my expense. I hired a different plumbing company, who used a camera and sewer snake, cleared the simple blockage via the basement sewer access, confirmed the line was in good condition, and guaranteed the work—for a fraction of the cost.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
