er)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107431757735451973389"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"","city":"","postal_code":"","state":"","country":""},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":false}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Scott Harbin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3bzsGrpKFKgt3xSnYZWyHZAn0Cd0mPIoWTrH_Y4Xnt4LorSX61w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"These guys are amazing.  Truely.  I would recommend them, and will even actively promote them to others.\n\nSean and Adam are amazing guys who work hard, are honest, and very knowledgeable.  They came out, spent about 45 min crawling around under the house and marking things outside for an estimate on a new water line and a sewer repair. They took the time to plan a better design, explain their thinking, and how they could save money by doing this different, but better.\n\nThey took care of all inspections, even dealing with the disastrous city of Redmond.  Full permits, inspections, extra days for a plumbing and a sewer inspection, and still came in as promised on the budget.\n\nThey cleaned up, protected my yard and property, communicated clearly and regularly, and we're easily one of the best contractors I've worked with in a long time.  A testament to their profession.\n\nDon't hesitate to call me them.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn310kBHA4Ap7JpXW4AZcE2kAb6r-7c89rsXmORjjRE0E0JNboUYquAS3pwYMS0W1I5Htt1BqN9d9nE0GH6o99VRtEO0kQxoMffVQe0UuE0c2JCjCJ2OA7A8kSD3_DNLPgW9np0L=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1g_NkBgOJ1htAWRgqAMdPdzO3cg1Vo_qobi9hyyNLek0BWfVbXV_KKr_l6DgwkpMvxDyNTJ3y2ZNnxG0HpviJWH6vGKcaDZbUxQ8clFRdW3USM5NZp4PEzickgN0ZmKgTHk6-q7Q=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2Run3z39Qqluo7JW44tsCenpTPWRkwdqLn1j_GJt9YvZCPj98kT6CS8V0h5LPDMWpdln713c6Rq23Z6GiDvJbj6xN1gJGNi-1zT0y_FrkU7nuyCaHBqr_xAVfzYSw4AEBEeVRV7Q=k-no"],"When":"2019-4-7"},{"Name":"Theresa Jerome","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTNd3_kZfpB2CosluvOPlLqRxha56pGkPIK174KGf_tGfCej3E=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"These guys are great! Came out and were able to repair our sewer line after another company dropped the ball - wish we would've called them first!  Their efficiency and quality work were instrumental in keeping on track for a project deadline.  Will definitely be using them for future plumbing and sewer needs.  Thanks for your A+ service!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kristian knocke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLVKzi1c1Jv2593eMfQmvbB6McqHExoIX9CSyUsVLwQHqb5_g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"These guys are awesome! My hot water tank broke and started flooding my garage this morning and I found this out when trying to take a shower... let me tell ya... nothing can wake you and piss you off faster then an ice cold shower in the middle of winter! Now running late and trying to get out of the house to get to work, I have no time to deal with the situation. so I call some of the big name plumbing companies that advertise all over the place and they can’t fit me in the schedule today. I called 4 places and started to lose hope of a warm shower tomorrow morning before coming across anytime plumbing. Sean there at anytime was very helpful and it seemed like he had a busy day already but he still stopped by got the water shut off and figured out what type of heater I needed. Then return after the other job that he had planned for the day already and installed the new tank for me. I am very grateful for Sean caring about my issue and rearranging his day to insure that mine would end well. I recommend him to everyone, this level of services is hard to find anymore.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emily R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVo6-oUdORl9m3JFxRs8CxKpiS9bVjyGBLYrwZT-kRJ2-vc9CZU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In the two homes that I've owned, and paid for services/repairs on, I have never experienced the level of care and utmost professionalism as I did with Adam from Anytime Plumbing and Sewer. My recent plumbing issue ended up being far more complicated than he or I anticipated - throughout everything he explained in detail what he was doing, and what it would cost. I cannot recommend Adam and his company enough. Do not call anyone else, I certainly won't.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Molly Drumm","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVLaeluZNzuwnGHZN_Q6thnkiJxUXJH5Fb2H0ZuEt3WVCXfg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sean is prompt and reliable.  Our water heater was installed quickly and efficiently and brought up to code.  When our new water heater repeatedly malfunctioned, Sean never made me feel put-off.  He took me seriously and went above and beyond to make everything right, even though that meant 4 or 5 more visits to trouble shoot and fix the problem.  I will always call Sean at Anytime Plumbing and Sewer for our plumbing needs in the future.  Thank you Sean!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Debi Marr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIe78N9-ZHZjzQZIHE7Jxyguhyj5s_UJrsKVnQXWNvfWR2Fzg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had an emergency and Sean was out within minutes and stayed until resolved. He and his crew are extremely hard working.  Sean communicates throughout the process and explains everything as well as making you aware of the associated costs which I really appreciated.  We will call Anytime Plumbing for all our future plumbing needs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ryan Roberts","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKOA6hWqm8vrupVsJkdLAmg0scRlxn4uc8n0V2H-_aZ5tcnEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My water heater was having problems and other plumbers were booked and wouldn’t respond to my house in Goldbar. Sean was very friendly and was able to come out and service my water heater for a reasonable price. I will definitely use Anytime Plumbing and Sewer in the future.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Krista Love","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVnIiuofbq6ZQLYgFPHk4kMgtyzsSOn0QIBZfQcd3P8NxVCPvmz=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If I could give Sean and his partner Adam 10 stars, I would. I met Sean a year ago when he worked for another company, and what I appreciated the most about him was his empathy. We were really stressed about our plumbing issues and the state of our house...he was completely non-judgmental and understanding.\n\nHe has since branched out to create his own company, and believe me, we, as consumers, are so lucky that he did! Here is why you should use Anytime Plumbing and Sewer:\n\n*Empathy. As stated above, he actually cares about what you're going through.\n\n*Experience. His grandpa was a pipe-fitter...plumbing and related professions have been in his family for generations. He already has more than a decade of experience, with all of the knowledge and contacts that brings. Note: If he recommends doing something, do it. He knows what happens if you don't.\n\n*Integrity. He does what he says he will.\n\n*Flexibility. If you have an idea, he will listen to it.\n\n*Commitment. While working for you, he is committed to getting the project done and done right, even if that means coming back out.\n\n*Fair pricing. We were shocked by how much plumbing repairs cost. However, since he's on his own now, Sean is committed to growing his business and charging fair prices. From our research, he charges around half of what the big companies charge (depending on the repair).\n\nThe most important thing for us is that we've found a plumber for life. He did right by us last year and also this year when we had the incredibly unpleasant experience of needing to repair our main sewer line - most importantly by making sure the work was done within the boundaries of his initial bid even when there were issues, which is not a small feat.\n\nWe are so grateful to Sean and Adam for their great work. We no longer have to stress about our plumbing situation and can move forward with confidence, knowing that if anything happens in the future, they have our back. It is a great feeling!  :)","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
