me":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":true}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible seating","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Ahmed Kortam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCcQRXv0sXCa-rmgmcpQiXovZoVMpLLnwcTmDjGo2_IUCufA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Fast Response, but Careless Work and Poor Professionalism\n\nMr Rooter was responsive late on a Friday and sent a technician early Saturday morning to investigate my main water line leak. I appreciate that part.\n\nUnfortunately, almost everything else about the experience was disappointing:\n\nThe technician was careless, unfriendly, and didn’t listen. He only focused on the technical fix and didn’t care about the condition of landscape. He left things too messy compared to how it originally looked.\n\nHe insisted he “knew” the leak location and wanted to break my driveway concrete without proper diagnosis. I had to stop him to call a leak detection company first who confirmed the leak was actually in the dirt area, not under the concrete. He didn’t have the right tools, and the work took two full days because of this\n\nPricing also felt misleading. He quoted me ~$5,000 including concrete demolition and repair. Once we learned no concrete work was needed, he only reduced the price by $500, claiming that’s all the concrete work would have cost which didn’t feel right.\n\nAdding to this that in the quote it was mentioned that the the company will Bed new connections with sand, Backfill and compact to rough grade which didn't happen\n\nOverall, while the response time was great, the workmanship, communication, care for the property, and pricing transparency were very poor. I would not use this company again unless these issues are seriously addressed.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2XA0e73OoS9JArSQgf13-gxFsQkzaazzzqJS5uIsMwBovUSG1r3czbE5EdcV8iXLEQo5qBeDPFLOW4XfU406tN8Y_tNloKeb312ZsmQLpAiX3NW5llVv8n5UFul-t2GIt2tlOIBmniEmEQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1-9ZBjdBnXn6LaKSP3ZTEJwbdfvhZi4slZxvMvI7uxM0zwNhxDDuue3c_6NJmDd51Aa3DBk9V8EQCm4E_B4SRBVWlWMowPqf9x31iRm_lUDYCJYSp7BeQTrLLDF3iWQa4x4y9rKftsGRHk=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-26"},{"Name":"Kristi Jacobsen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLddbLnkAIE8Omce_4uHjyEtAKVu50pFKnxOMHFbN5YstwrWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Aric came to our house on Monday night (2/2/2026) to look at water heater replacement and came back Tuesday morning (2/3/2026).to replace our water heater. He did a fantastic job and very clean work!  I would not hesitate to work with him again.\n\nThank you!\n\nJerry and Kristi Jacobsen","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"DeeAnn Peltier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKtlpnNDxX898_GER9lGIEp8NRpLFrIeBVwgoXL1XLikcMUsQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Alex was a pleasure to have in my home working on my clogged sink. He was pleasant, knowledgable and skilled. When the work was complete he not only left my kitchen sink in great working order but it was also sparkling. Great job!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marian Ullman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWsC8zR0ONCxVKWUXwsV_nZmJISFj0--MlmRad5UpdZbJDppSiZ6A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I called with no running water in my house at 8 am and 20 people coming for Christmas dinner at 2pm. They had someone to my house in an hour and a half. He did a wonderful job and left everything spotless. Crisis averted and Christmas can proceed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rob Anders","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlKTxkPkH7-bsP44qCfSP0bu1Wy8k2X-W6GHXY4LhS_cDgnw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had them out on very short notice to remove a gas line for a stove at my parents home (they decided to go back to electric).  They were very fast to respond and perform the service (called on Sunday and service was done Monday) and communication at every level was excellent.  Permit was obtained in a very timely fashion too with very quick response also from City of Lynnwood. My parent send their thanks!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ed Jones","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocImF2WTL6K5WNGEpH-wUGhSeWMN3vvTtq4qe-dJrKrjSizW=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I just had surgery and we had a blocked sink in the basement that I would normally try to clear but I cannot do it in my condition,  a very courteous young man came and took care of the situation with ease, the area looked like no one had been there , it was so clean. I’m very happy with the service and how everyone I dealt with was so polite and professional.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"JENNIFER bourgault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJcPlLwq6Aa5iKuSbT5zQ-OZZb6tqwdrFSLZ-vLtiThsXUbXrMK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Knowledge was outstanding.  Tommy explained my new water heater how it operates, how to drain it. He gave me the exact amount prior to installing the new water heater.\nCleaned up right away. Thank you so much , we appreciate you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"carmen miller","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrRvc0b-L-3w9N9s78r_WOcaKn1_oYAGYGupIDB7hEPFbnjRiH=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"These guys did a great job! They were friendly and explained all my options very well. Came out same day and got the job finished.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
