 I asked Sean to take a quick look at a leak in my home. Without hesitation, he was open, willing, and happy to help. He really took the time to listen, checked everything carefully, and showed great problem-solving skills. The leak had already ruined part of my drywall because the builder’s pipe connections were poorly insulated, but Sean’s up-to-date plumbing knowledge made a difference. He explained the issues clearly, walked me through my options, and made sure I understood everything so I would make an informed decision. He not only fixed the leak and redid the piping, but also installed a new  shower head and handle so I wouldn’t deal with the same problem again. He truly went the extra mile, his hard and sincere work truly shows. I’m extremely happy with the results. I finally have peace of mind knowing everything was done right.\n\nThank you again Sean for your work!!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn02ZH70FL612xrxamYtrRq6xPtp_zuo1aNfumc7WZSCKQO0CPGhVsKIE3CT9DJdP_3Ex2Lz7AUsgOqbnzEfTuzMfjssrK_YG3BBPsh0ku8RYsfp8WCNR6W0-x3PbJyD6QasFN8OGsk81YfZ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0FaEqQ2VyWUtuLp7hDDO1J85W0SmVX_VyhzfavRE2nIAsOfGza7aFIi-wEmgDecLMC6Y-DQ1dclnJImHhJaOOjpsgv1sDDXsDSI6cbEJKSfUtD2QDxzZgs-qtl16yz4agcgnf1PVxGpyY=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn20gdTD1ltAKW9DJIht_fefL5KQQwigkdUrMlaL4B_N3m-89qMN4nwaFL7F6ql63KoyBBaIxOpQh4rnQcJbUTw_Iu0pTC4O0NBYl6gQ1glntN3fAFUQXKfxIB3o40FNtQjxAH4ph2N-oK6O=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2jaP6FcUIcNdKne4jx1OubyNXjvOXqKqWTUIymrT8iAvGVbaygPJ56J7untkVhLMyL1kW67Y2SlxQKfk0cvsM62c-d3NJdGfgQU408E2vZkJEyjURGStrIEs1OlsscDZt4sGxB_3_XajwN=k-no"],"When":"2025-11-23"},{"Name":"Ramana Marshalla","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyaRJCIuXzRIyzITdxWQwHb2GsrkezR-bFxBLl96E72cXE258W=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Sean from Puget Sound Plumbing and Heating came to help within two hours of me calling for a plumber today (a Saturday). He was friendly and knowledgeable. He located the leaking pipe after asking me thorough questions about my observations. He cut and removed the back of the cabinet below the kitchen sink to access the leaking pipe. He ensured we’d found the only leak by switching off and on the main water supply to the house. He quoted me the price and had me sign off before the cabinet wall cutting and before the pipe and valve replacement. He helped me learn about our pipes. He was clean and efficient. The price was way more than I expected but according to google it seems par for the work done. I am completely satisfied with his work. Great plumber help!! Thank you!!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3taJag8bDXDtFMpqFWuGIv7kg2iUaNdbDQHs3YdqRoj6X7RRiCeoxb-F2bb4KswaEnNgK9fN9B3R4fPmVu5Ak7gn1ByEKOAMAA_CSrKSLtyZcq6vayAeDPAQdpyMVYzZIMtTpZZZCnam5B=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0ZkXuEJKbcR5blHccpfmTkYiR4ERZ9cOsF5Ap3CFm3KkJMsP3kCgUmYIL4AEetXQ79vYqXqDfdkyLy-2krYKk9Z5qe1M0KXMgEsr4Pz9THsoO8aOHwCwYpmE1U0s1hbgazjJsvSgSPTn5a=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1Eff6zETkCDPlpGo0F-DHr7dJ4g-WUs4bHSfFrtRiwjoGB-J-HQfGn2J3DUt5WI1gbgXtDj-YuRMxAZJSQum7ccyxtjA52lvWNaOyo_q8QBYnjhtpy7MQGTfaxH6z6GXipE0af0HKTaJ1A=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3-lsNKFH92lbbMkBCuiLFQyYEsb0_W8WP_TZH6s7h_e4WegFzdDQEvK97_FgzSp6KdORV5JORii6M_S0nBR4r5gxDvve0vvrkzMn1YnmsJw9CZjt1ky-0hNAfnZRhE9jCPm2qEdpyhWoHf=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn32vx8qkMnpZ6xrPihK-MwQwcSQo4o-q3kSyTXWmZy2MAVF0Pv75uwqceDrw7SyngMKPemaOAOcAXSbiXm8_TgSHxUWtk2quz7u2XMOaXo0zpY7dHbW_k6q7C_-ZuFIxHRbibadFeOdTBgj=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3CkGa6p2mjPZfHAvdlaEtR_lxDUTQnUfGntNkVdEwgJAipgqyjZv2QnX7OJkswlRKWMtBBhU3R7msl_W7Gcs7-I9ufDEm4SbLL7eforjT8QDNh1LSEt1OW9g3izgVbLyQpzZzt5ohDPjvY=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1lEs8SMGdIRxyjBYHUsDP_8r6yndf5vKTdSXEV09FE8eopsj9GeeQyYEfyqqjRrJk37WSmEn_tIxVhkze6bmopfFdZ8IiyFHp5MYfj4oXp4MVFC44sIzcS-Fw0sWYKFE5df-X92iw-mV1M=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0arw9z2c1o3EPK1ynMs_VZagKzMzZ05fXZlTHNI8JIrfiWjfqBLfqRgCGQen89KBFFxrABlKwLx7tiM9XyYuYCwTpT20Ni81d96zO1cmMzOwG0Q_TVGo7agifoZsJzX7mZVD17HNwES8o=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3LX6f_EVVTTq9qeG_VawJ2Dz1tzpLEQOH8nYIMqf888Wqg13TF4Eu9FLBbrtQXe8n_ZAYrn-QAr0Ij0Sn8flf89MTJ6bbUUmOD9u0-xpjZYEf2mXgUH1Xt7oI_T4VcPFZxaUDAw8Zmwew=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-25"},{"Name":"Edna","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSShI6uczAeFJ9nO5WPYu_CdlpsVs5-sR3Dbg4Gx9FsMv-lQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a leak problem and I called Puget Sound Heating and Plumbing.  Michael Lawson,  the plumber was dispatched to do the job. Michael was very professional, extremely knowledgeable,  great listener, very polite and installed a new toilet without wasting any time.    We have used a lot of Plumbing Companies and dealt with a lot of plumbers and we have to say we were impressed with his work and knowledge. We would highly recommend Michael Lawson for any plumbing Job.  He is truly an asset to this company.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cara Gonzales","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLD8oQGd6MnGWLdZV09zMY8pwlNpm9FJQT2Y661nUPDgbZ3qg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Michael came out and did a thorough check, verified my water heater needed to be replaced and gave me an estimate.   I had a previous estimate that was lower he was able to match it and get the water heater changed out in no time!  I appreciate his workmanship!  I will recommend if ever asked","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mary Waring","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK2zB5dSVN1485FTmep42p7KDq8D1O81SeYRaYUQT8zNQ8u=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We were so overcharged by this company last September. We had just bought a midcentury house in West Seattle and wanted all the toilets reseated, because one of them was actually tilting when you sat on it, and the others all had crumbling grout around the floor, which didn’t inspire confidence. After looking at the four toilets, the plumber said one was fine, but reseated the other three, and also fixed two small leaks under bathroom sinks. He was a pleasant guy and seemingly did a good job, but then we got the bill. We were charged nearly $3000 for 3 or 4 hours of work and no major parts or materials, just new wax seals and grout. Well, lesson learned! Today I had a different, well-reviewed local plumbing company come out with a journeyman and an apprentice. They spent over 2 hours reseating the fourth toilet, the one that the plumber from Puget Sound Plumbing had deemed okay. It wasn’t okay, it was leaking sewer gas through the bad seal, and reseating it turned out to be surprisingly complex. Cost was less than $1000.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lia Fakhouri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWbVLI1sdvwDTlzH06kEHXEfezLwBGSmJki9C30cDc2peiWysc1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I had a blockage in my tub and sink and needed someone to come out ASAP.\n\nSean the technician who came out was excellent, very friendly and talked through my options, he was also very accommodating to take care in the bathroom as it was newly remodeled.\n\nHowever the pricing was absolutely terrible. They didn’t share anything upfront when I made the appt just stated it would be by the job.\n\nThe ‘by the job’ pricing was way higher than hiring a plumber by the hour. Since I was in a bind I had to move forward with them but for example and transparency they charged $1000 to snake my kitchen sink when I paid a plumber from another company $250 to do it because it took less than an hour. Also snaking the kitchen sink didn’t solve all the problems as we had hoped,  so they charged an additional $400 to snake the tub and see if that would fix the issue.\n\nLikely will not use again although Sean was wonderful. Not a good rate for simple blockage fixes.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nick Hubeek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIutKvTY4kp31ynAsHzQKMW268iRUCtNk2ffAaeWf3YW2IUzA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had a leak coming through living room ceiling. Spoke with Chris on the phone and Adam was our technician.both were courteous and treated my issue with same urgency that I felt. Adam was efficient, neat and great to work with. He quickly found the issue (upstairs shower) and found both a cracked pipe leading to the shower head and the bigger problem (leaking around the shower handle/cartridge). Adam did a good job explaining what the issue was and fixing it quickly, even with 4 crazy kids running around and a toddler napping. He left the space cleaner than it started. I really appreciate the job he did today.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2gpEhEYm-8pUfwnclEC4g_UmnzgUdYGMtNWYfhUSf-36pwqHJHIA_FKSL5uqSr8gyqe1F0mFUgzOMMptYQ5oU3FYXfKXh5iAkyJU3jmYzUzTjTeAUuqDIORcyuKFQ5Yb-WABIhzybQgT1p=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0BMGziN-TLGhWWGCm9DLwEwm9KYHmS-XOGuz5DqvcKxeP_n2PF3EHsBV7DboIVrD4-74Y5to4OZ2vnf7pRtZzR_gNHyamVhZBTLPD-mM9cDSkGWXRWqmlsGqC7e7W9h9G44TIur1_LhjbZ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3j063La7P5-G_5rwfd7liGGkKIgGvMMCzp2u_d__qQkHRekaiHr3Kko_-9DYG5Zeuwkd0EhfZxCkfLwVyc8cdj5XSwYY9H7CsRWta5FvuX4wQ5PQ4bg7YoPHXfMMTnByKfVb9ZfXLB7YRP=k-no"],"When":"2025-6-18"},{"Name":"Matt Francis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXG-7Cyhec_5IeF2fXsIgHic92II8PcOCgE2hTqXgdSvEXsXvPJWg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good service, but expensive. Puget Sound Plumbing replaced my water heater (non-emergency), and while I’m happy with the work, the price ended up being ~$500 more (+17%) than a reputable competitor (4.7 stars on Google). It’s my fault for not waiting for the 2nd quote to come back before agreeing to Puget Sound’s quote. I confirmed that both companies’ quotes included the same Bradford White water heater, an expansion tank, drip leg, etc. In fact, the competitor’s cheaper quote also included a water alarm for the price. In short, this is a good company but I recommend getting a 2nd quote before selecting them.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3swJhppCa58SlThcdSnGN8aQyLEIEWNIzJ20oGFXzyJO253HvPLhwjQMJldKK8gu6R-NjG0DOH8cDL_BJ5yK2uvYbm1Rur87hhSbsebdmz_1fqKUbapY2LUoyZlJz0XXx7fNRQofVRQRfU=k-no"],"When":"2025-9-9"}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
