elchair accessible restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"amenities","name":"Amenities","options":[{"name":"Gender-neutral restroom","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]},{"id":"parking","name":"Parking","options":[{"name":"Free parking lot","enabled":true},{"name":"Free street parking","enabled":true},{"name":"On-site parking","enabled":true}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Adam Clark","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVifUynuNVgBqbIb_jlSqi84_3LD0XZjYwY09hn8oO00o_P0CvI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We worked with JD and Logan on a fairly comprehensive project that started with what I thought was just a drain cleaning. We eventually discovered a failed drain line under the concrete slab of our 1960s house. The team was very thorough in understanding the problem and working with us on coming up with a solution that minimized the repair bill. Rather than routing along the existing failed pipe, they ran a new drain line down our hallway, avoiding two tiled floors, and a fully finished shower. Job was completed on scope, on schedule, and well communicated throughout. We definitely will be going back to Stollwerck for our future plumbing needs!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anne Hurley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVMgmi1oVGwnnRjjBJhVHVQ9lhTPJ2AIP5B7KL-p4JsKSXJ2QE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"JD Stollwerck is a fabulous plumbing company. They are professional, knowledgeable, flexible and super responsive. I feel so lucky they have been willing to come over to Whidbey to help me with my projects - their service is so thorough and reliable. I highly recommend them.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lee Stringfield","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX686BxzkiH7HGdrRX39fv_v4qoMminYGVA7FmycF46oxjkQuM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I used to use Apollo but they got extremely expensive, not to mention less personal as they've grown in size. They arent bad but Im looking for something else. Figured I would try Stollwerck. Glad I did. Not the cheapest, not the most expensive, but they do solid work and you can actually talk to the owner, everything was honest and straightforward. No suprises, and the quoted price was accurate. Thats what you want in a plumber.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Richard Ramey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWR5Z2U1tSegR1obpkjQzaqCRPt302AJLXt7Sa4NkOCgz05w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve had several great experiences with this company in the past year and they’ve always delivered excellent service. The owner came out personally for my most recent job and handled the installation himself. He was very responsive, explained everything clearly, and had a new water heater installed the same day. It’s rare to find someone who is so knowledgeable, dependable, and genuinely cares about doing quality work. I couldn’t be happier with the results and highly recommend them.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"DEBORAH HARRISON","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_6KQk5GiQMNC6EdDTc7cAkq8ry-dsjzcJgCyGBJBtn8LbLQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stollwerck Plumbing was very professional in every aspect. JD was helpful and informative concerning our main water line replacement or repair options. This local, family run business has lower overhead and charges less than the larger companies. Logan and his team did a great job preparing for the line bore while protecting our property as much as possible.  They kept us informed and asked for our preferences several times during the 2 day job.  We appreciate their expertise and friendly coordination!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3rPBjggN2MPpInfeUCp9WufAtVNBOvn4LNArNk8Rwy3lYNjLoWjguLsVFjZ9xXx-4stUDp956lbuKJ2RhPkkI_8vodXX40uu4xT5un6YmWiF-KeY5785p8qs-X4gj1fzPLRkzD=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3NOREGa1iNuzNHpm7ZH2fd6owiycQwAHcqjYQ1mXXvYKvYmcnmXfUn2dVIRtpknLOfa9Za2mp8pqnl1xsXgCg3i5orM-LUAz86SN-pq8Fxnl_-5SkIH7_ekxtu9_8eZVZWSvhiwA=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0wICEmlI14ualytKu0XNr1vOYltXM4rmG5NiN_0NE1W7MAvkkyRjfzJY0WFQcbPDuX2hYoXE--2mco2nBvyRhVLBg4zyZq0J4D512qR3m8I7N-cyVmf_iDtqEW3lJwl60wym8=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0Oz0Ytjqz-Mnz3SN6fmxIIQjVRHl8anXRik1DLZTemyqwRKbDp_3he_kA5KOvm82NIOK9Am2R_Qhn_SLqjuce1_iUhaicLjRlYRf6I9hKhWT-Acs3MPn61VRdBOWCt2g4ZWx8tNQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0KPAyvdPz1cwELG4oL-3gVBgnl9aPh2cPOVIL3ZMi_Eb2WW70lW5jM8DDUWbxIA8iEnmvfBPag3aXzhZm2DD7Z_xHPQuaRG8FqfdJ_ubN2WGPLRRIGbz08xOazErb8uui--uEt=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1e9SVZZJeWx_0tCUwSkasXeXSqcsaGdhEPztwVr2DHSv7c8O3ZS6MFmVVqvJITdAcmpu-rKuZHxVSGAqpKQnv144pEKIHT1SmPagRrJuU1GU-Npc3u3trG5csAvmusDoVflX0lEA=k-no"],"When":"2024-2-22"},{"Name":"Caitlin D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWYdA1lKaLTW5qdjpRorB9nkeJIQ0OQPJA2PBgjr1FjNhu2uG5s=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stollwerck Plumbing helped us with a unique 20 year-old brass faucet that had forgotten how to behave itself. This was not the easiest of tasks because of the age of the faucet. A new cartridge had to be sourced, and, of course, was not in the same state! The part arrived, was installed, and we have hot water in the downstairs bathroom sink again! Thank you!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mark S.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLIlBdhvs7083Aw8tK0JzjZydrWBuHX0rFrfgPUSXb2NaMXhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Update: 8/28/23\nI had an issue with my Pressure Reducing Valve (PRV) at the house (leaking) and overall low water pressure. In June 2023 I called Stollwerck Plumbing again and they gave me a fair estimate to replace the PRV compared to two other plumbing service provider estimates.  They sent Collin again which made me very happy since he was so knowledgeable and experienced and did such a great job fixing the water meter leak in March of 2022.  JD, the owner, was very thorough in trouble-shooting the low water pressure.  He even called the manager of the Everett Water Utility to ask them to check my water meter to make sure it was working correctly. JD was so professional and helpful and went the extra mile to get to bottom of my low water pressure issue - which turned out to be a city utility issue since I live at the top of a hill. I really appreciated his follow-up calls to me on my water issue. Collin installed the new PRV with no issues or leaks. Nearby plants were protected and clean-up was excellent. I trust Stollwerck Plumbing to do a quality job for a fair price.\n\n3/16/22: I noticed a leak near my water meter about a week ago.  I looked up Stollwerck Plumbing and they had great reviews.  JD from Stollwerck promptly came to my home, assessed the situation and emailed me a written estimate that I approved via email.  Shortly after, I was contacted to make a service appointment. Collin and Cecil showed up, quickly assessed the situation and were ready to work. They dug the access hole laying down a tarp to collect the dirt and keep the sod for reinstallation. I watched as they worked hard the entire time with no break.  Collin was very experienced and knew what he was doing...taking care to not get any dirt or debris in the waterline.  He also knew a lot about what parts to use and not use to implement the repair.  Cecil, the apprentice, was knowledgeable about excavating and taking care not to damage the remaining waterline. Overall, these guys were pleasant and polite and didn't mind my questions as I learned about how to repair my main waterline. The entire task took about 3 hours. Result: A successful repair with no indications of any leak and a very satisfied customer. In addition, Stollwerck Plumbing sent me a thank-you card for my business and JD and the crew all signed it. Great customer service. Yeah, I'll call these guys again if I need to in the future.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn168Swaq5VLVNjW9ENorEGKZKJZ0A-ZAii6jjFylbXoHX99Tg-nveOYIdQ-nAp3PvA5nG9wZOhbpHtQ266vbXyFiDFfQYNu88ZL4fVwuXwUIgrSeHNzi7A7wmkkcu5DcEIIjsRkSQ=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2jPqFZ0P_06MA-JBqulm7IzlRU2U-KxxPDxAqRU0k7xzNxpFQioMPltrjUv-6amebjckG5NdWQHW5NaV7-jg2Z5_HxWKeyyO4qiKXzTec9XxU-QqpPA7EbWHsM2jBSB6lq9pI=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3I4hwpgh5fIZVGOnxWIDkRlw7JKXvcCP95mL1bmJmFReZ5YX_BPXfDkm9gNffxoFzDytrAl8jst06j5_6Mce4bZ2WA2me4Vgd0YjIW2uAYMCTkVfGoib5ymPMeceDA8E5ZehvBxg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1ItjJNhjPYLyFozf9869XZ_11gDc5Pz_kEpAYLRw7F9NSnfsYihBxRPfeYfAU-Im7V4bQqKsYg7BW2rvB7QGmLcYw2BWPwdjqvb-bhY0279pr8vWoQzxb9KqvwKal2YhyhiKo=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3YE_flzg8IulBNhvxIoB0_PqXB-zrvMOpkCnzmGjok9kWg8joLRNAADw1UEf1cx5-cZZlNXwbb9PFxmBwoXsO28DuMxo5S5142ETLhR7d05bXCZleVLlxG0CM14da97eJr-Bm7=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1HTWsQnxr5WnSux319uIMjZWVMPQKA12NrgvKc3GV4zQrtiXMupniViQOq56TnwN5ZkG1aVb3r-FqpSwKu_YKkiHquBtkah8vk0WCM7JsS66B7WhA-w7eGyt0AIZDIUV73q6ei=k-no"],"When":"2022-3-23"},{"Name":"Matt DeGooyer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjIgobrzBrbLwrfkbW2ddN7UHNQaCZV7I8wmLzLnp4m8UgeQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have used Stollwerck a few times in two locations, including on Whidbey Island.  JD the owner is extremely friendly, professional and we were very satisfied with the quality of the work.  In fact, we hired them to fix poor work that was done by another large company in Mukilteo that has big vans with advertising all over them.  Pricing is fair compared to other plumbers we have used.  We will definitely use JD and Stollwerck in the future.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
