SIHqL3GT7aoE5pm-AKOR8Wa_oloqVo2HGqdq--ShJTCpH0E9VifYgh9LuMIvzvW778EV1motM3Z8qfpW70eO90klGa4iE8EWd0POjNfu8pQyVAlGJq1gnWQ4fM19JFjYqdDr=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3oEyQHPocJ3FlSkdgbbX8sAAcVq8swmenZIFqfiFTT_TKl8aAoYZ4iAgXpa7OCPVCGgcHXZKKTM101fDzP9SZGNDi44RxDaQ_c4IanWN9jnRZsG2jKSy8eWJplDL7ZHo9vfqLf3vreWGOv=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-10"},{"Name":"Ward Urion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlBp6V9MXtKmPDEH3XH4AflnIsm3OQiZ0pJ0LTHtWN8o5Iw7dC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First to call in response to my web inquiry. First on the scene to get our hot water restored through a great tankless water heater on the same day as the inspection. Might not have been the cheapest (don’t know…couldn’t wait to find out) but I trusted Eddie’s assessment and recommendations. He treated me fairly and most importantly he did the job well. He even discovered that our main service valve was in its last stages given the reduced pressure. Now we have endless hot water and much better water pressure. I’d recommend for sure. All of it done in an afternoon. Pretty sweet!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patrick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInZNZGuWblOmgpNpGMfLi8j1BbqHuyiNyG3-RhPx4Lu4qOegk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Probably the most comfortable experience I have ever had with any plumbing company. Paul and Travis came to inspect a leak that had developed from a second-floor shower. Bees was recommended the water damage restoration company. Both Paul and Travis were very transparent, honest, and took the time to explain all the work they were going to do.\n\nThey also took the time to look at my other pipes (sinks, bathrooms, etc) for any apparent problems (complimentary, and they asked my permission before doing so). Lo and behold, water was also leaking from an important pipe in the basement. Water had begun pooling but this was caught early thanks to them.\n\nThey were able to get an estimate on the spot, and the cost was quite fair for the work they had to do and the time they spent (multiple hours sawing, cutting, crimping, etc). Throughout the process, Paul explained what he was doing and let me look and ask questions - VERY important for me to learn preventative measures and save myself time and money in the future.\n\nOverall, the vibe was that there was no attempt to upsell services or push for subscriptions (common with other contracting companies). I say it was the most \"comfortable\" experience because it was clear they were just there to do the work and share knowledge without pushing, cajoling and most importantly preying on our lack of plumbing knowledge. That was seriously dope.\n\nAt the end, we paid by card and there was NO expectation or even option to leave a tip on the tablet. I chose to leave a cash tip and it was clearly not expected. Pretty much could not have felt better about the attitude/vibe/honesty of the contractors (Paul and Travis were stand up dudes) which reflects well on the org itself.\n\nTL;DR felt very comfortable, encouraged to ask questions, given accurate and unbiased information, efficient work, 1-year warranty, clearly not a high-pressure burn-and-churn sales culture. Appreciate it!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3SLV0uHFMF1qRqj612vp_gdG8SPAfiKNoIn3vNnfimy_4HDwp-TRfYv0m77SlHYdxLdqIwR4bcXaibGTLmVV6cPdPyiO1gjD3x_3OyCRvLPI1iK4tDFGqX_6DMEg1bhWsggF6n5VmOu8KK=k-no"],"When":"2026-3-10"},{"Name":"T Keegan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIDcWRY4nJsGmXDWg2hO_I27Ia4HIlCSM3KJlmroU5X1wgN1Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time customer with Bee’s.Tonight I had an incredible residential service experience with Milan from Bee’s - best in over a decade. Had a water issue that i was expecting a typical service call out 2-4 weeks. I called at 2:30pm and had help at 5:00pm. Milan knew what he was doing, was extremely pleasant and engaging, and worked thoroughly to do a great job at their bid price. Over and above service - a rarity these days. Use Bee’s - I’ve hired skilled trade workers for over 30 years and these guys are among the very best.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kiana Sonnenfeld","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKVC5KnbSqVPYKDyVv9Bl6wVJXYOgp_6kE43zuS16ZFMKiEFaEZ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had an excellent experience with Niko G., the technician who fixed a leak under my kitchen sink and replaced an entire toilet in the bathroom. Niko was professional, friendly, and clearly confident in his work. It was such a relief to know the job was in capable hands, especially since I know very little about plumbing. He even stayed late to ensure everything was done correctly, which I truly appreciate. Niko went above and beyond, and in my opinion, he deserves a bonus for the outstanding service he provided. Thanks Niko!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3hVRnqXYcxGZgLSSNFHLaBg-PjdcYjNCuJZX2iPPktj4SNN_6E1YrHwsO14Qq6IR9iYmi3MlwqRMJEoNXB2E0G0WgHuEAsF313PfnhyDbTTnE3TwCwFN956p7dsjLWn4Vj-79vC97oevvd=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3IM8fNdPCoNRWa52-VKCDIQWp2jkzom1Q7YmV8NK1wMIlpFdtzNZiv6RD2MaMQWU7hs1M5dYmkn5uB8e4mZwHHWf5qc9oPeDDXeYPYGi9tvDp7q7vBx1578bFEF1qaljxaT3-EGDUTfNw=k-no"],"When":"2025-10-2"},{"Name":"Bart Shilvock","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL_He8bQdMNAWq4MUD2IzzSkaTg6GyrRAJ1xCdLhSObhRDDHRI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was my first experience with Bee's Plumbing and it will not be my last. The company was very easy to deal with. Got a plumber (Andrey) out very quickly. I needed a couple things, including a PRV installed, in an area that was so tight it required some re-routing of existing pipes. Andrey did a great job. Was very professional and was able to overcome a challenging installation.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
