eat, was quoted 1k more by 2 sons plumbing \u0026 Bee’s plumbing. They have the same warranty as the other quotes. Plus, they are  local. I found the other two companies. We’re trying to upsell me, and it turns out what they were trying to sell me on, was not needed, or required by code. Millcreek plumbing was honest, and I appreciate that. They also offered an upgrade on the anode within the water tank to extend my warranty to a 10 year. However They told me it was not needed because our water quality is so good in the northwest.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1wM88sc6So8Cvc5ZBtNKTGpfYNGeKP2Eb7K4Q293oKmNNvKOwVVU0DiS2ALUuj14JIUpTiNBpM6ja1o8C_FR_FtgpV1XvuMrNaV_dAvpB6DYyiyzh7gr2N-tCqJK2s66ASXyoZ0SwOlood=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-22"},{"Name":"Michael Carey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLlv3naJez-aGtNytCS3X0mt6hebYhY2tcvG7oj5AhZeCBklA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, am I impressed! The professionals at Mill Creek plumbing helped me on a Friday afternoon to fix a shower in my wife’s bathroom. They arrived within a half hour and had the repair done by the end of the hour! I am definitely using these guys for my next repair!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0-FscktfKe-VeFKcW4lpYALPRdrXHb9-LKFF6ZtKBTpNE7Trf4AQ-jSWI-fbD7TUBZ6zp1PtyIAQrbjvUBWtqdD2vojwooUPzlj4SOrjGcaD-ouA9OVMSgkGChk6_9AJZMp-hGeYwc-aE=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-16"},{"Name":"Kathy T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjULi_O11GAK8xzYeFqRB4Fmu8VSnJa3ShCBCaVw_le2kbeVhUdg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic experience with Mill Creek Plumbing.  We needed a gas line capped off to remove an old gas range and Jon came in and got it done quickly and competently.  Everyone we dealt with, from scheduling to the actual work done, were professional and pleasant and the price was very fair.  We will definitely use them again if we need a plumber down the road.  Thank you, Mill Creek Plumbing!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mary Murray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9GvuX-L5KTmdVhVg8JnuKDU5RPPG7qQ9lVxeXxVMvbn37fg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We've used Mill Creek Plumbing for all of our plumbing needs, big and small, throughout the years. They are fast, reliable and skilled. The one issue I had several years ago was immediately rectified beyond my expectations, at no charge to us. The new owners seem to be carrying on the tradition, and I trust that we will be relying on them in the future. Today Sam got through my laundry list of rather minor issues in no time at all, to our great relief. We also got a pro tip on reducing bio film in our sink drains (hydrogen peroxide). Thanks, Sam!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sue Bomengen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGKsQB_9X6c4tMh6HsBIiXX_zsYtZeNCrpPwyNwNr9C6tQMHkM0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tried Mill Creek Plumbing for emergency kitchen sink and D/W leaks.  Called Mon. at 10am, had a Plumber by 1pm!  Great customer service. My Plumber, Sam, conqered the leak mystery. Great investigative work. After three different fixes, I was able to put my kitchen back together.  All fixed up by 3pm!  Thanks, Sam, I  appreciate you!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Edward Graff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW8QfClJm4nwjKWsEKqsYVPAvi0zaP0y_NoqUT_kSDNW9Ghr_U=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Ouch, $435 to instal a bathroom faucet, no parts involved and time spent was well under an hour. To be fair the service was quick and efficient and the tech was competent and professional. The install was $285. + 95. to come out, even an $18. charge for 2 paper towels, a pair of booties and latex gloves (no gloves were used).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Krystal Dhondt Chamber Director","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW27376ycsJt5Y9lZLilynMAXTAnzLlC2w4E9EKYwhlbld8T-2x=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mill Creek Plumbing was a dream to work with. When my hot water heater failed their response time was great. Fred the plumbing tech was professional and knowledgeable. He made sure I understood exactly what he needed to do and why and exactly what the cost would be. The job was completed quickly with high quality parts. The work area was left clean and tidy.  While it’s never a great day when you have to call the plumber I would definitely recommend Mill Creek Plumbing. They made everything as quick and painless as possible!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Robin McMahan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVz1hvtglFPcHowrYBhYkKvP61Qi9m1bxwHdHSawKvDwEUCeEMH=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was leaving out of state for a 6 weeks, when the water district said they saw a rise in our water use, when typically, for 20 yrs, water use was low. I was impressed how smoothly this transaction and repair was done, especially with several obstacles to go through with communication through other people for access to the house and property. They found an older drain back faucets underground pipe, by a 2nd building, had rusted and was the leak.  Timely solution and repair. I was very satisfied with the entire job.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
