 plumbing issue. Highly recommended for your plumbing needs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nathan Carnahan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKQhSxzpdxnVXvkrowrYAAKSkn_osRMyGxc45BqnpOVtM9R4A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I got a recommendation to, LIMITLESS PLUMBING, from my plumber after drain field failure. With a 55 years old drain field I was told I was very lucky. BUT I was being forced to connect to the sewer stub that the county had installed 25 years prior. Can't verbalize how shocked I was the cost of just the permit was just to connect to the stub.\nI called Limitless and Brandon answered within three rings. Luckily he was doing another job not far from my house and stopped by within two hours. He seemed very knowledgeable and confident while inspecting old drain field out flow and septic tank. He gave me a rough estimate and a possible time he could start.\nI wanted to call around and get other estimates before committing to Brandon. My neighbor had to connect to sewer years prior. He had given his installers name and number. I gave him a call and was told he wasn't able to do it at this time. He did give estimate and similar to Brandon's estimate. I had asked if he knew Limitless Plumbing. He said he knew Brandon through the plumbing business and said he a was a \"good guy\". One other call to another plumber and Brandon got the job. Other plumber was $3800 more and 2-3 weeks out.\nDay #1 Brandon started the following week and by locating the sewer stub. Easier said than done. He dropped off his excavator over the weekend to be ready to start. The water district tech sent to locate the stub dislocated it by 4-5 feet. Luckily with Brandon's experience and contacts he was finally able to locate it.\nDay#2 Brandon and Doug showed up right on time to start the trench work. Doug was in the ditch directing Brandon around the waterline and underground phone and cable times. In which they were ALSO dislocated. I was very impressed with Brandons jumping into the ditch and being hands on.\nThe rest of the job went with out a hitch. Brandon had the old tank pumped out. He removed the lid, broke it in half, and back filled old tank with pea gravel. After back filling trench and tank. He processed to smooth out the effected area and brought in top soil to replant grass.\nNOTE: Other plumber was going to charge me additional $2600 to lay top soil \"landscaping fee\". Brandon ran a little short of soil and drove back to Snohomish for more top dress soil.\nIf you want someone to give you a reasonable price. Show up on time and lead you through the procedure of installing a sewer line. I definitely recommend Brandon. Very personable, communicative, and knowledgeable.\nLIMITLESS PLUMBING\n5 ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn30CZor7gX_gAo3iHve2-FWolIPNzcoxP9TsrqL3qlHRhLlk4dvsFj-BEg6qMDEkuXBRXTdlu6urahB2xw_gOgGaSmeQ_6AGbdjDCRVgV2gdnf1C15fnmC1_nzSkw_bsSgtmppp=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3xMQEJCLgQXV5yNcGUy2L8bcCNH67f0ABANUs_M6G8xua0iVOIcEsDNrWuv6ct56eEnXL143iWQpSyuxgXUOZLC7zRQvNtA9IRYpvpn00V4sASyIKTIC0HDMso70QX0WhxB5GMLg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2KyGb7YR_4q88jgYvo3619MWp8elqkZvmuXH-R9UHzw_Fr7ArWQYYDsKoTHjsQMev5RnJAWSs4Q4WkznyxoGM6e_15UATXiiIlkF1n_bCWuqhy9qg_fWX8MSx7wstluk9bgI5D=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2YANmqooBWnMlOgUisbrXH1hFMOrDX11hwZCAVbAIE8UR0aEWnQ162wCYr_f_Ferhhj1oMZQdpffru81Sh5khKvMIDCkdgXwDRryj5mfcAhnI2UUJ9juF4TI4jXO0YqbYi3KzU6Q=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2yioevaaAKuKj_h-i71CipP6iXwZ3fT-8ULngEPpNIUUdlX0_ZPYO9l3OWIzusAkvdt0Kqp_OPdR8ymSCuzEk9xmD4IwuO2gc1Iy3ZFq2SeKUHcY1QjCGH0XnFvVKHpDUAJZkg=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3tZIe4oY-Yc_RqR_pIGDZun4uUlC0QHzfKYh6mOxWQxzXaDgxh3JciV_GrIN_ASjYDaamPKiKcH6_5N5rQ6GZV0vpVrip0TrabW3wghm2HHRHEaZq5SQ8zkQk7UdMRk5CA4LxO=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxo