a3=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Jerromy Fernandes, is exceptional in his service, leadership, in educating us on what he was about to do, why, and what he found every step of the way, all the while communicating with all those he and we needed throughout the process.  He walked the property, assessed, communicated, tackled the issue with precision and care, even looked into the crawl space in the dark to gather more data for his calculations. He pushed to the end! Thank you Jerromy and Roto Rooter and to our incredible landlords for your expedient search for a solution and on New Years Day! Excellent job! Very appreciated.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1POCWbTZbPOv1Z_Q6IcB6MURCWu_aeVCOGtn2Y3M-SNFUL8Yei0IaEHYG1GYvdi6PlUrTJJhmC900yf8h-yOB-yQQUslguKpJGHBUIg842OBp9Dq0NlH0AZxFKmIJMWp8PaIPh0pQbpj8W=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn0XTvdgVFhAYRApjrokP75qUeL0Vd0YCqb60sxTmBr8Sq_BmEJFs6YbVxBbRhkmOMRot43bcJsQUGBy4hV1IgyITb9myHKocQnpXJQLUHvuyilGY6dpPZNTGyMON0nOtk_KBzzpjJMbjjNB=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn3RQ3FvSVX9OhKO9sKB6XMPnT91cRreaJiTelCdCcj-bvQcYXx3P4Acm06lGsm-YQSpH98r4WMv5YHIrdE3u4aS8S00Nt8fHFKQoMZVHd7q8-HC4sfpa9a3BM6pJg_cuifPUthJCuYEt7WW=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-2"},{"Name":"Erin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI5RQxSJQ4zTgn2CuIkzGXtM4rYt9j7JJaYYWrbZ3CqBIVSKm0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was having issues with my toilet and the toilet was actually backing up into the bathtub and it was horrible! We have a septic tank \u0026 I've never been on septic before in my life so I had no idea how they worked or how they ran at all. I contacted Roto-Rooter and within less than an hour, Jesse \u0026 James showed up at my duplex in Lacey WA. They were polite, friendly, down to earth, easy to talk to, very informative \u0026 explained exactly what the case was \u0026 why it was doing what it was doing. They actually drew me a diagram of how the system worked \u0026 what was happening \u0026 why. I really appreciate Jesse taking the time to do that for me. So they rectified the situation the best they could at this time because right now without getting into the septic issues, that being a whole separate issue in \u0026 of itself. They made sure to throw on some shoe coverings before they walked inside of my duplex \u0026 they explained to me \u0026 my daughter both what was happening \u0026 the reason why. I really appreciate their professionalism \u0026 how quickly they showed up! They fixed the issue for now the best that they could \u0026 hopefully the rest gets taken care of as it should by the owner of our property. I really appreciate them coming out and helping the situation as it is right now. They were both amazing, very professional \u0026 showed up promptly which was nice as well! I will go to them in the future if I have any issues in this department and I will recommend them to anyone else having these types of issues as well! Thanks you guys, I appreciate you coming out here and helping the situation!","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn2-_C0A9ql6wk_zWOwOSZTw5f1wcpKraDa7BwGKAKUxyMtbmy0cd75YXJXV4yVfw6wxcR3pZzUE4pYJWHy1Qu3ANtvp3ptRCWOfIsGzCbu_oCdLZK5Lqfip4Y9W0PARfHjhxksiqdFxV2Gt=k-no"],"When":"2026-1-26"},{"Name":"Piel Canela","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL1c4ho911Y8bgqJFwfOxYPdbEWn_9lHoqLDlmfXCYOBSJtxg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Britton was a pleasure to invite into my home for him to evaluate potential water damages.  I am thankful for his time and words of advice.\n\nRoto-Rooter has the best employees I’ve met on n along time. Tim also visited my home for water heater issues and he is simply an amazing person willing to explain and give advice.\n\nIf I has my own company, I would ask them both to join me.\n\nThank you guys. Many blessings and Happy Valentine’s Day.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"gg loff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJtnPGwXnzawnn61i8gy9UZp0W99DWSRRTg14YdYshK_vMgVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The tech was great, but the service was way overpriced by Roto-Rooter. All the did was pressure washout our main line and put a camera down to take a look in less then an hour and charged us over a thousand dollars. The trch (nice guy) let us know if it took over a hour they would charge us an additional thousand. I wonder what the manager and CEO of this company make a year! I would have looked for a smaller family owned business had I known this in advance and had more time. Will not be calling them again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"徐琳雅","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKiD3u-jS4Ls3HLXcECn21pLW4_Qsfzs0A3eu3_9PFvJ6_uVw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"\u003c$700 for service and $300+ for the new tap.\nFlorin (Ray) is very nice, chill and professional. He also provides me some knowledge about maintenance and how to do some simple fixes by myself. Nowadays, the plumbing service is always expensive, but we are very glad to have Florin and his great and fast service! Highly recommended.\n\nps: the office person, (sorry we don’t have your name! ) who helped us with phone scheduling was also very nice and quick. Much appreciated.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
