rib/109240359102055782296"},"complete_address":{"borough":"Highline","street":"2000 S 116th St","city":"Seattle","postal_code":"98168","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":true},{"name":"Onsite services","enabled":true},{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]},{"id":"accessibility","name":"Accessibility","options":[{"name":"Wheelchair accessible entrance","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible restroom","enabled":true},{"name":"Wheelchair accessible seating","enabled":true}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"Tanya Slonecker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3zwJAMqCYllZ5gH_XFy3CQkD8US3ED3wwThjZGQ6s2eX5Axnb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A sewer pipe burst on a holiday weekend at my mother’s house. Mr. Rooter came out right away and had their team working from start to finish. They cleaned everything up and fixed the problem. They were all very professional and kind. I highly recommend this company. They explained everything with clarity and gave us options. I hope I don’t leave anyone out,\nKen, Atama, Arvind, Solo, Brian and Suk, I can’t thank you enough!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Julien Brundrett","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWqNza1DH8Llk98-q1vqCTzlJVac8GDlYyRDqgxg6mBrg5db2RpCg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve had excellent experiences with Mr Rooter across multiple appointments. The technicians are friendly, professional and very thorough. I have high confidence in the work they’ve done in my home and they’ve won my business for the long term. No it is not cheap, but no reputable plumber is cheap. They’ve been on time and prompt, and I’ve been able to schedule work done typically within 1-2 days.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Katy Hart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVW_T882je-meDXhHKTG4zrbj81DUSUrmFf5SPA35JINFULSgU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mr. Rooter to the rescue! We have been loyal Mr. Rooter customers for plumbing needs at two properties. They are always polite, quick, and know how to get the job done. We have also found their pricing to be fair and scheduling is a breeze.\n\nThis week we had Daniel and his team (Pablo and Latrell) out to our home to hydro scrub our side sewer in preparation for a home sale. The crew was quick, left our back yard clean and tidy, and they provided a video recording and images of their work for us to give to our realtor.\n\nDaniel was available via text as well, which made communication easy. 10/10 would hire again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Norman Armstrong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK8Ajf3NYg7P31WmHWlqHONkD9L2ert7Bd47CH-BFuW5oVXSg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Do you ever have one of those experiences with a Company that blows you away. I had a kitchen drain back up and I filled out a couple of service requests with some well know companies. I won't mention names but after tonight it's \"Bye Bob\".\n\nAnyway. Mr. Rooter called me right back and said same day between 4pm-7PM. Shaquille showed up at 5 and went right to work. Every company needs someone like Shaquille. Smart, courteous, explained everything he was doing. He was careful about not making a mess and really cleaned up after himself. I wish every service call from any company had a Shaquille. When he left both my wife and I were smiling. She had her kitchen back and I witnessed a 5 star service call. Thank you Mr. Rooter and thank you Shaquille.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Richard Ehrsam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqLYBJ8YIsZkC-9GLefUGVt4WhIHW3Zg2a0EDr5Hp1Ohmev29e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mr Rooter rerouted my kitchen drain from an external failing concrete 3inch line to a more direct to the stack route through the basement between the floor joists using 2inch pvc.  it works perfectly.  It looks clean and sturdy.  Aric S., who did the work, was efficient, polite and friendly.  I was pleased that he figured out a way to  install it without causing an overhead obstruction and still be to code .  lovely work. very happy to have a working kitchen drain.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael Edmonds","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUOoB5L2FVqBADcFR1MIYkvyqUXWKT3NyR5lmBDFnD36_CczgrE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Robert was efficient and friendly. He outlined the cost clearly before doing the work and there was no commitment to do the work beforehand because they don’t charge a fee to show up. The work was scheduled and completed all within the span of a couple of hours.\n\nI’ve now used two plumbing services in the area, and this one feels like it provides a better value for what is paid. Thanks so much for the assistance!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jennifer Sasahara","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeAphqKYbkA_-Ya1nZ20Xtx7avSxqzEaNGt5rbfNb8Uzd3uzEXjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We share a side sewer with our neighbor who was having some back-up issues. It turns out both lines had heavy tree root intrusion issues. We were able to schedule with Mr. Rooter quickly and easily to come out to scope our lines and give us recommendations and an estimate. Brandonn H arrived to our residences on time and he was very friendly, professional, and knowledgeable as we had many questions. He provided us with a very detailed estimate, and even gave us a couple of options to select from.\n\nOnce we decided to go with Mr. Rooter for this work, we were able to schedule the very next week which was great news. Brandonn kept us notified every step of the way via text and/or email and we were able to ask follow-up questions very easily.\n\nThere were (2) different crews out for the 2-days of work, but all were very professional and able to inform us of the work being done and what to expect. The work was done in a reasonable amount of time, and the inspection was approved without issue.\n\nOne of our fence post caps was damaged during the work, but we were informed right away both by the work crew and by Brandonn via text. Brandonn later came out to replace the cap, and we're very happy with the overall process, the work, and our decision to go with Mr. Rooter.\n\nHighly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Joanne Mackey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-PRQ2xpDkhxPeyh5k4bl1_9RBKysnNbmfe9v8TOmsCMZs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Problem was discovered upon arising on Monday morning and repaired by lunchtime!\nFriendly and efficient.\nUp front pricing.\nRaymond, our tech, was knowledgeable.  He diagnosed the problem right away.  When there was a snafu, which was neither his fault nor ours, he apologized and set about correcting it.\nYes,  we would call Mr Rooter again.\nThank you","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
