9_YXKSJQxMM5URKKJ3OgGaP7H7X8Z1WFgCsPyJeX6zA=w224-h298-k-no"}],"reservations":null,"order_online":null,"menu":{"link":"","source":""},"owner":{"id":"115573703150343430791","name":"Campbell's Quality Plumbing (Owner)","link":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115573703150343430791"},"complete_address":{"borough":"","street":"12818 123rd Ave NE","city":"Lake Stevens","postal_code":"98258","state":"Washington","country":"US"},"about":[{"id":"service_options","name":"Service options","options":[{"name":"Online estimates","enabled":false},{"name":"Language assistance","enabled":false}]},{"id":"offerings","name":"Offerings","options":[{"name":"Repair services","enabled":true}]},{"id":"payments","name":"Payments","options":[{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":true},{"name":"Credit cards","enabled":false}]}],"user_reviews":[{"Name":"KEVIN CLAVADETSCHER","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIF_JMie3IxEOnoq_43e9R6NgPsVSbuMYC4PHWQAyGyEWZvTg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Chris at Campbell’s Quality Plumbing was great to work with. He installed a pressure reducing valve (PRV), fixed several plumbing connections, and installed a new water heater for us.\n\nCommunication was easy through text and calls, and I was able to send pictures ahead of time so he knew exactly what was going on. He was professional, gave good recommendations, and the whole process was straightforward. I’d definitely recommend him to anyone needing plumbing work. I will be hiring him again for our next projects.","Images":["https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1KB_5J_KechuJjWTu6v4vk8ROE8yLa_WOFahffAfqGSbTiw0v8PF72kgpTsYrSUMkEC2HGSui6-9w3AZ6O1iYwXUy1iEdqz-5G6oE6QsFB7LbcZanqXlj0_XfqqaJS-FlRXtV-sfyZANd9=k-no","https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/grass-cs/ANxoTn1FwRE2baGDXAPSMaaPJ7b_TxUCoAPrZia0XfzwHmVEoRVh-5f3VB80punIZ7XE-orqGDzQJX9Ramp0GVGPttVe09EhWwE15Bk9GBNTitVOsZRmd9XEBB-Obfehruy05LzNQ2u0QWqotKQ=k-no"],"When":"2026-3-10"},{"Name":"Carlene Hoff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK5WMuccpN8X_Y-i7ZUFXjkRqyy8s9F6QQI-CZFOLVGQ3j4xA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Chris and crew @Campbells Quality Plumbing are the best. I was given a bid by another company with this huge scope of work at a very high cost that was so unaffordable and a lot of work that didn’t make sense to me.  I did know some of it had to be taken care of, so Chris and crew came to the rescue. They told me and showed me what needed to be replaced and why and the next steps. They were fast, thorough, and clean. They did such a fantastic job that was affordable. I am so thankful and I would highly recommend them to anyone! Thank you so much!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Manjula Prakash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-WP4EQh2fH1Ws7PieyGtuMhZ7G5p2SnzQicjB6miBiGttmG4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Campbell's Quality Plumbing, the best plumbing service. Chris is an amazing person technically experienced and  licensed. We have been using his services since 2020. Chris and Trevor did a great job with all our plumbing issues in the past. He's well communicated and does a great job.\n\nFew days ago we had a leak below our laundry room, Chris and his team came within minutes after called. The leak was from our washing machine and it wasn't a plumbing issue at all. Chris recommended a restoration company to help with the water damage.\n\nChris went above and beyond helping us on a Sunday, by coming all the way to just help move our washing machine from the laundry room to the garage coz our washer is super big and heavy. I greatly appreciate his help, I have not come across someone or any company that would go an extra mile to help like Chris did, even when it had nothing to do with plumbing at all.\n\nI definitely recommend Chris and his team for any plumbing services. They know what they're doing and are the best...","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeanne Kennedy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIFnd_fXCDDcR38oS4891Gl_Uuh5pY12JCrXx4zBTy2H4DZ3w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Campbell Quality Plumbing replaced all of the copper pipes in my crawlspace. I had been given their name by a neighbor as fairly priced, timely in completing the work, and aware of the disruption this work causes.  Chris and his crew were all that and more! Clear in explaining the work and the costs. Seeming totally experienced, easy going and very kind, fixing small things he found without charge wonderful service!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ArieTE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLgANC-PmAWF4ARaCm-vg_HXzmMlA-IWyvMKRVMaAjIIaXNNA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We did a full house repiping to replace our old CPVC.  Chris and his crew were amazing!  This was a huge process with lots of (original construction) surprises, which they handled easily with open communication and professionalism.\n\nChris was always upfront and transparent about what the work would entail+cost, and gave us options on how to handle complications as they arose.\n\nThey went above and beyond to ensure we were in the best spot possible and were super nice.  We felt like we were in the best hands possible for this project and highly recommend Campbell's for any plumbing needs!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melanye Navarro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJz3cWeY5bl3B3Kb6ubkoHSrqQpMW3P5Kc7XI5-5MNOeLLgtw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had an amazing experience with Campbell’s Plumbing! If you’re looking for a reliable/efficient plumber who won’t overcharge you, call Campbell.\n\nWe had a major plumbing issue, a leak caused by a faulty toilet flange and some other pipe problems (I won’t pretend to understand all the plumbing details). We first contacted Apollo Plumbing, but they quoted us an outrageous $23,000. Wanting a second opinion, we reached out to Campbell’s, and we’re so glad we did. They not only completed the job (plus extra work), but they did it quickly and efficiently for just $6,000, about a quarter of what Apollo was charging!\n\nIt’s safe to say Campbell’s Plumbing is our new go-to plumber for life. We will most definitely be referring to everyone! Don’t gamble, call Campbell!\n\nThank you again, Chris, and your team for all your help! 💞","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Colleen Maute","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK9_i-pEPIZTHphtpPcMCdHi5e6jzGZIXJy2vxKm2p0I5-dMg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Chris was great to work with. He was prompt, communicated well, and fixed our issues in a timely manner. He identified issues that other professionals missed. And his pricing was very reasonable. So happy!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ariel O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3mMLx6LY--uDncCqrqEH-xGbSKoLU2zLoju_R5nfuzEOcaOaN=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Chris and the team at Campbell's are fantastic. They have helped with a variety of projects around the house including a new water heater, setting up a utility sink, and plumbing an undermount sink. The service is friendly and the price is very fair. Chris was also super quick to help when I had a pipe break after a winter storm and his emergency pricing was very reasonable! Super happy to have found a plumber I trust.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
