de me feel at ease because of his knowledge.\n\nOnce work began,  they kept me informed. There were two crews onsite to start the project (Melvin and Chris) everyone was on the same page every step of the way.  There was a small change on our project, but it didn't delay the completion.\n\nI would highly recommend!\n\nThank you, All Seasons!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Keith B.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIrw4lWHO2iQGFMY4PuXBlA09-hxjM2dpIYGHLLxQjaFhEYAA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Mike and Dave (Two Feathers) were true experts in their field, and it was a pleasure to see how they used their problem-solving skills on my home’s drain issues.  I would call on them again without hesitation.  And the cost of their services was very reasonable.  I was attracted to All Seasons as a family-owned local business and they completely met or exceeded my expectations.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kenneth Millson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRUAXtjIavYzqr6LLW3HKejxOIny5koeuCdHYrPgtjX2R2NjSX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great company to do business with from start to finish! Their folks showed up on schedule for the initial inspection and the actual work. The estimate was clear and covered all the work to be done. The crew explained what they were going to do and did just that. They took great care protecting my space around where they were working and cleaned up well. All work was done according to the estimate and done well and at a very reasonable cost.\n\nI highly recommend All Seasons Waterproofing!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Barrett Lavergne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFLFs15-ZP0KPhYgWy8Fm0Lxg3CQcpZCIvq1TcZqA1Z71jPn4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"From start to finish, the entire All Seasons Drainage team was knowledgeable, professional, and attentive to detail. I received bids from several companies, and they were by far the most thorough and thoughtful in both their evaluation and proposed solution. They designed the most efficient and effective plan for our situation, and the quality of the work showed throughout the project.\n\nI was especially impressed with their care in restoring the landscaping, everything was put back to its original condition, and they even returned an additional day to correct a walkway without hesitation. I would absolutely use them again and highly recommend them.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ed McKinley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVVtRDRsdVvQcDaDry0Y8Ang13NtlcHfSYh8Dnycv88egPW-IA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"These guys were great!  We had crawlspace drainage problems and All Seasons responded quickly and the job was started within two or three weeks. The work was done quickly and efficiently and the problem was solved!  We have gone through the wettest part of the winter and there is no longer any standing surface water under our house. The crew was very nice to have around, and the exterior portion of the job was cleaned up each evening.  Over the years, three out of four of our condo duplex units have had All Seasons fix drainage problems. We highly recommend these guys.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Allison S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKpRYwWKNPag6dzNDMAc78zLoZyiNK9gTmAtLM21C2Yg8pQsPI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big thanks to Mike from All Seasons Waterproofing for his deep knowledge and investigative thinking.\n\nWhat truly set Mike apart during our initial visit was his attention to detail and his willingness to understand the source of an issue before recommending an expensive solution. Rather than pushing a fix right away, he suggested a thoughtful “wait and see” approach while gathering more information—something that likely saved us from jumping into unnecessary and costly work.\n\nHe took the time to walk the property with us and explain how water moves across the site, then offered practical, preventative suggestions such as improving gutter and downspout coverage, routing water farther away from the house, and flagging a nearby city drain that wasn’t functioning properly, along with advice on how to contact the city about it.\n\nWe were especially impressed by how detailed and specific his knowledge was. He even explained how trees contribute to water absorption, complete with precise figures for how much different trees consume each day—both informative and unexpectedly delightful.\n\nMike was generous with his time, clear in his explanations, and genuinely focused on helping us understand our options rather than selling the biggest fix. Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Steinberg","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC-MAV5yvPNOqSPynqRnD_tDbDjcK281t9CcHmfmOunEdxHqqd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bradley and crew were excellent! Great communication, super accommodating when it came to how things were installed, and asked all the right questions with regard to preferences. They showed up on time and worked hard the entire time. And they protected everything and cleaned up really well after. A+ all around!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Julie Carlson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCvwvhj0LR-ITqihaqVNIAPF5Ao3MrGNdOGUI23zhFTZe2aYH_QA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had All Seasons out to look at an issue with water seeping into my garage which is built into a hill. For reasons that have nothing to do with them, I ended up not having the work done. However, they we're very nice, \u0026 even came out a second time when I had more questions. On the second visit, a manager came as well to make sure my questions were answered well, realized that it would probably be more work than they initially expected because of a couple details that were missed, \u0026 told me this but then said that they would still honor the lower cost of the original bid. I also found their prices to be comparable to the other companies I had look at the potential work, and they were the only one that offered me a design that could potentially solve the problem without using a sump pump because of the area that was most affected and the angle of the floor. It was nice to know there was an option potentially that didn't require any moving parts","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
