onsive and got us scheduled as soon as she could.  The technician, Benton, was very thorough, respectful of home and communicated with me about the process. He cleaned everything, fixed our furnace quickly and made sure everything was working before leaving. Great service!  I will definitely use them again","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"12 Peach","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhEECxfsfIN5ZG0ZZFkaOj7XexY5-ff1W9FQEm5ugfpwZSdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Bob's Heating \u0026 Air Conditioning replaced our furnace and heat pump 3 weeks ago. Technician Bryon did a perfect job. He was very professional. Our furnace is located in the attic with very tight entrance. Bryon had to remove the attic entrance's frames in order to get the new furnace into the attic. After the replacement work done, he put the frames back without any mess. The new system has been running for 3 weeks now and we're very happy with it. Our latest utility bill was significantly less than prior months'. Thank you Bryon for your great job!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Heather Yen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwgtIZo87tJP07GCbQTEEgSS6bEfw2pBzjpigwFzQWReFSTSia7g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had a great experience using Bob's Heating for furnace maintenance. The technician was on time, professional, and discovered a leak that needed to be repaired. He was patient and answered many questions, seemed very knowledgeable about the system and potential replacement costs. We were given a quote for repairs and were able to schedule for the following day.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tani Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKnZXGzaeSvm4jBLIOi9sGeN_V-e6lGbL2MHIK6Y5G1kTi1vA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've had excellent service from Bob's for five years now -- both routine preventive maintenance and urgent repairs.  Recently Nate and Kailen had to make multiple trips to fix a challenging problem with my three-zone system.  They were so professional, friendly and knowledgeable -- and patient in answering all my questions -- assuring me I wasn't doing anything to cause the problem!  As usual Rachel's reassuring friendly support on the phone keeping me updated and believing they really cared about me was a huge comfort!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lan Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_L5-KI_C7Z7qDfC1xlmYYUcXBdp1yQcZj6QhCBiaD2y-Bu5rY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently moved in to our new home and some of the room seems colder than others. Jerome our service man was very thorough in making sure that I know how to operate the system. He spent more than two hours adjusting and inspecting the vent and ductwork. Thank you Bob’s heating \u0026 Jerome for standing behind your product.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Miles Wallio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyjGwi0S4JutSjK2G2xpGMFmwPrJ4rr8uaWeqccjPLth9YB4p9_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had them come to perform some regular maintenance, clean the vents, and descale my tankless water heater. The service folks were kind and considerate. They explained everything they were going to do and why. The team covered their shoes before entering the house, and the house was cleaner than when they left. They gave me some guidance on steps I need to take between servicing. As a new home owner, it was beneficial to know how to keep things running smoothly. Overall, top notch service. I would use them again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Khrum Kashan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLCmVAAxczeGshP9pZ-vFxoLctbQyGRR_xMG2S7XRdsRqERX-Mh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Excellent Service from Bob’s Heating : Special Thanks to Kramer\n\nI’ve been a customer of Bob’s Heating for over five years, and they continue to impress me with their professionalism and quality of work. This time, Kramer handled our yearly maintenance and service call, and I couldn’t be more pleased.\n\nHe was extremely professional, knowledgeable, and thorough. Kramer took the time to explain everything in detail and went above and beyond to answer every question with patience and professionalism. His attention to detail and clear communication gave us complete confidence that we’re in good hands.\n\nAlthough there was a short delay due to part availability, the team kept us informed and completed our annual maintenance and service smoothly.\n\nI highly recommend Bob’s Heating and if you have the chance, ask for Kramer. He truly represents what great customer service should be. Thank you Bob and Thank you Kramer !","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hyun Kyoung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrk8Nmar1X_UZ-bXBDTIdAoAl1zZvHetRDU4Nbusn7Ks9sS1eN=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I learned about this provider from a community Facebook page and trusted they would be a reliable provider. We were having issues with our heating so I called and scheduled with them. They said it is cheaper if we did a bundle for diagnostic/repair/maintenance for both heating and AC. We would get a 10% discount on parts if parts were required. They said repair was a flat rate and was included in the bundle and we would just need to pay for parts if it was needed. It wasn’t cheap but we needed a service anyway so I proceeded with it. Their tech came out said it was a filter issue and no parts were needed so they did the cleaning of the system and normal maintenance. The next day it stopped working again. We called thinking that the labor warranty would cover it. They said if a new repair was needed we would get charged for the repair and parts. Even though they already charged us for repair. They said they will send a more experienced tech out. Their second tech I think did try to do a more thorough job but he didn’t know exactly what the issue was and needed to bring a senior tech out with him. However wanted to charge us $300 for something that he wasn’t sure was the issue. I did not feel comfortable proceeding with the work not knowing that they would resolve it. He also wasn’t able to fix it that day and we would need to schedule it again. It took them one week for them to come out to begin with. I went with a different company and they figured out the issue and thankfully I did because whatever they thought was the issue before was not the issue. I normally don’t write reviews but I literally felt scammed by this company and explained they should not claim they have flat rates when it isn’t in fact a flat rate. I let them know I would write a review and would not recommend them to others. There has to be more transparency with customers. We are all just trying to get by and already pretty stressed with no heat. Doesn’t help when they can’t give the reassurance they can fix the issue but yet have a price tag to it. I would avoid Bobs if you can because it’ll probably save you a lot of time and money.","Images":null,"When":""}],"user_reviews_extended":null,"emails":null}
